# PowerShell Script Standards

## Every script must include
1. A header comment block describing what it does
2. Error handling with try/catch on all Docker and network commands
3. A final status summary showing ✓ or ✗ for each step
4. An exit code (0 = success, 1 = failure)

## Style rules
- Use Write-Host with color: -ForegroundColor Green for success, Red for failure
- Use $ErrorActionPreference = "Stop" at the top of every script
- Docker commands must check container status after running
- Never use curl — use Invoke-WebRequest or Test-NetConnection instead

## Verification pattern (use this in every verify script)
function Test-Endpoint($url, $name) {
    try {
        $r = Invoke-WebRequest -Uri $url -TimeoutSec 5 -UseBasicParsing
        Write-Host "✓ $name" -ForegroundColor Green
    } catch {
        Write-Host "✗ $name - $_" -ForegroundColor Red
    }
}
